        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Obtain an ObserverResultT&lt;T&gt; for the given instrument, that can be used to record a measurement on said instrument from a multi-observer callback registered with Meter::RegisterCallback. The instrument <emphasis>must</emphasis> have been included in the original call to Meter::RegisterCallback; any data points set on other instruments will be discarded.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>instrument</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The instrument for which to obtain an ObserverResult. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>An ObserverResultT&lt;T&gt; for the given instrument. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
